item.dc:creator: @dogzound5 dogzound5@gmail.com
item.description:
@dogzound5 wrote:

127.0.0.1 is your local network address and that is why you can connect. There are several reasons why you may not be able to connect with your real ip.

Are you trying to create a server?

A static ip address is really needed if you are creating a server because a regular dynamic address changes every so often by the DNS but static is one address that your ISP provides you and it identifies you as that ip forever lol
